## Example vm.args for a release embedding Livery.
##
## Livery caps concurrent in-flight requests at the supervisor level
## (the `max_concurrent_requests` application env, default 10000), but a
## library cannot set node-wide ceilings for you. An edge-facing node
## should bound the process and port tables so a connection/request flood
## cannot exhaust them. Copy the relevant lines into your release's
## vm.args and tune to your host.

## Maximum number of processes (default 1048576). One per in-flight
## request/connection plus translators; size above your expected peak.
+P 2000000

## Maximum number of ports/sockets (default 65536).
+Q 1000000

## Maximum number of ETS tables (rarely the limit; raise if you create
## many tables).
## +e 8192

## Do not let a crash dump land in a world-readable working directory;
## point it somewhere the operator controls and can scrub.
-env ERL_CRASH_DUMP /var/log/livery/erl_crash.dump
